# gpsim command script: PIC10F320 POWER-ON-PRESSED startup case.
#
# WHAT THIS IS
#   The companion to footswitch_toggle.stc, covering the ONE startup branch that
#   the released-start scenario never exercises: the footswitch held CLOSED
#   (pressed) at power-on. debounce_init_context(PIN_STATE_LOW) brings the device
#   up in BYPASS / RELEASE_DEBOUNCE_WAIT with the counter pre-loaded to
#   RELEASE_THRESH, so a switch that is stuck or held at boot does NOT spuriously
#   engage the effect; the effect may only toggle after a genuine release + a
#   fresh press. The wrapper test/pic/run_gpsim_power_on_pressed.sh parses the
#   snapshots and turns them into PASS/FAIL.
#
# HOW IT IS RUN (see the wrapper / `make test-gpsim`)
#   gpsim -i -pp10f320 <variant>.hex -c test/pic/power_on_pressed.stc
#   Variant-agnostic: only RA0 (LED) and RA3 (footswitch) are asserted, and those
#   are identical across every output variant (the analog-switch drive polarity
#   flips only the RA1/RA2 control pins, never RA0/RA3). Running it per variant also
#   confirms each variant's init-time blocking actuation (the relay/mute ~12 ms
#   bypass pulse) does not perturb the held-at-boot path.
#
# PINS (per bypass_mcu_pic10f320.c)
#   RA3 = footswitch (input; high = released, low = pressed)
#   RA0 = status LED  (LATA bit 0; high = effect ENGAGED, low = BYPASS)
#
# TIMING
#   FOSC = 16 MHz -> instruction clock FOSC/4 = 4 MHz -> 4000 cycles per 1 ms.
#   PRESSED_THRESH(8) low samples register a press and RELEASE_THRESH(25) high
#   samples re-arm; the relay/mute drivers also block ~12 ms (~48k cyc) per
#   actuation (including the init bypass pulse). Every checkpoint sits well clear
#   of those windows so all variants have SETTLED by the time it is sampled.
#
# SCENARIO (switch HELD at power-on, then released, then a fresh press)
#   cyc      0..200k : PRESSED at boot -> stay BYPASS (RELEASE-wait), NO toggle
#   cyc 200k..400k   : released         -> lockout drains, arm for press; BYPASS
#   cyc 400k..600k   : fresh press       -> toggles to ENGAGED (the only toggle)
#   cyc 600k..       : released          -> effect latches ENGAGED
#
# CHECKPOINTS (the wrapper keys on these exact === labels ===)
#   PON_HELD     @ 120k : LATA bit0 == 0 (LED off; held switch did NOT engage),
#                         PORTA bit3 == 0 (footswitch read as pressed)
#   PON_RELEASED @ 350k : LATA bit0 == 0 (release alone does not toggle),
#                         PORTA bit3 == 1 (released)
#   PON_ENGAGED  @ 750k : LATA bit0 == 1 (fresh press toggled ENGAGED, latched),
#                         PORTA bit3 == 1 (released)

stimulus asynchronous_stimulus
  initial_state 0
  { 200000, 1,
    400000, 0,
    600000, 1 }
  name fsw
end

node n1
attach n1 fsw ra3

break c 120000
run
echo ===PON_HELD===
porta
lata

break c 350000
run
echo ===PON_RELEASED===
porta
lata

break c 750000
run
echo ===PON_ENGAGED===
porta
lata

quit
